<% title = "Ovulation & Fertility Tracker | Women's
Health Hub" %>

<div class="container py-5">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-8">
      <h1 class="mb-4">Ovulation & Fertility Tracker</h1>
      <p class="lead mb-4">
        Track your fertile window, ovulation days, and fertility signs to
        maximize your chances of conception or for natural family planning.
      </p>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Your Fertility Calendar</h5>
          <div
            id="ovulation-fertility-calendar"
            class="calendar-container"
          ></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Track Your Fertility Signs</h5>

          <form class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <label for="trackingDate" class="form-label">Date</label>
              <input type="date" class="form-control" id="trackingDate" />
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6">
              <label for="bbtTemperature" class="form-label"
                >Basal Body Temperature (°F)</label
              >
              <input
                type="number"
                step="0.01"
                class="form-control"
                id="bbtTemperature"
                placeholder="98.6"
              />
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6">
              <label for="cervicalMucus" class="form-label"
                >Cervical Mucus</label
              >
              <select class="form-select" id="cervicalMucus">
                <option selected disabled value="">Choose...</option>
                <option value="dry">Dry (infertile)</option>
                <option value="sticky">Sticky/Tacky (less fertile)</option>
                <option value="creamy">Creamy (becoming fertile)</option>
                <option value="watery">Watery (fertile)</option>
                <option value="eggwhite">Egg white (most fertile)</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6">
              <label for="cervicalPosition" class="form-label"
                >Cervical Position</label
              >
              <select class="form-select" id="cervicalPosition">
                <option selected disabled value="">Choose...</option>
                <option value="low">Low, firm, closed (less fertile)</option>
                <option value="mid">Medium position</option>
                <option value="high">High, soft, open (fertile)</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6">
              <label for="ovulationTest" class="form-label"
                >Ovulation Test Result</label
              >
              <select class="form-select" id="ovulationTest">
                <option selected disabled value="">Choose...</option>
                <option value="negative">Negative</option>
                <option value="high">High (getting close)</option>
                <option value="peak">Peak (ovulating)</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6">
              <label for="libido" class="form-label">Libido</label>
              <select class="form-select" id="libido">
                <option selected disabled value="">Choose...</option>
                <option value="low">Low</option>
                <option value="medium">Medium</option>
                <option value="high">High</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <div class="col-12">
              <label for="fertilityNotes" class="form-label">Notes</label>
              <textarea
                class="form-control"
                id="fertilityNotes"
                rows="3"
                placeholder="Record any other fertility signs or symptoms..."
              ></textarea>
            </div>

            <div class="col-12">
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">
                Save Fertility Data
              </button>
            </div>
          </form>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Understanding Fertility Signs</h5>

          <div class="accordion" id="fertilityAccordion">
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingBBT">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseBBT"
                  aria-expanded="true"
                  aria-controls="collapseBBT"
                >
                  Basal Body Temperature (BBT)
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseBBT"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse show"
                aria-labelledby="headingBBT"
                data-bs-parent="#fertilityAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    Your basal body temperature is your body's temperature at
                    complete rest. After ovulation, your BBT typically rises by
                    0.4-1.0°F due to increased progesterone production.
                  </p>
                  <h6>How to track BBT:</h6>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      Take your temperature immediately upon waking, before any
                      activity
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Use a special basal thermometer (accurate to 1/10th of a
                      degree)
                    </li>
                    <li>Measure at the same time each day</li>
                    <li>Record your temperature on a chart or in an app</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    A sustained temperature rise for at least 3 days confirms
                    that ovulation has occurred.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingCervicalMucus">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseCervicalMucus"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseCervicalMucus"
                >
                  Cervical Mucus
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseCervicalMucus"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingCervicalMucus"
                data-bs-parent="#fertilityAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    Cervical mucus changes throughout your cycle in response to
                    hormone fluctuations. These changes help identify your
                    fertile window.
                  </p>
                  <h6>Cervical mucus patterns:</h6>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Dry/None:</strong> Often occurs after menstruation
                      and indicates low fertility
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Sticky:</strong> Thick, tacky, and white or
                      yellowish - low fertility
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Creamy:</strong> Lotion-like consistency, white or
                      yellow-white - medium fertility
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Watery:</strong> Clear, slippery, and stretchy
                      like raw egg white - high fertility
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Egg white:</strong> Most fertile type, clear,
                      stretchy (can stretch 2+ inches between fingers)
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    Egg white cervical mucus typically appears 1-5 days before
                    ovulation and indicates your most fertile time.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOvulationTests">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseOvulationTests"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseOvulationTests"
                >
                  Ovulation Predictor Kits (OPKs)
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseOvulationTests"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingOvulationTests"
                data-bs-parent="#fertilityAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    Ovulation predictor kits detect the surge of luteinizing
                    hormone (LH) that occurs 24-36 hours before ovulation.
                  </p>
                  <h6>How to use OPKs:</h6>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      Begin testing a few days before your expected ovulation
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Test at the same time each day (afternoon is often
                      recommended)
                    </li>
                    <li>Reduce liquid intake 2 hours before testing</li>
                    <li>
                      A positive result means your LH is surging and ovulation
                      is likely to occur within 24-36 hours
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    Digital OPKs may show "peak fertility" when the LH surge is
                    detected, while traditional tests show a test line that is
                    as dark or darker than the control line.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingCervicalPosition">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseCervicalPosition"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseCervicalPosition"
                >
                  Cervical Position
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseCervicalPosition"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingCervicalPosition"
                data-bs-parent="#fertilityAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    The position, texture, and openness of your cervix changes
                    throughout your cycle and can indicate fertility status.
                  </p>
                  <h6>Cervical changes:</h6>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Low, firm, closed:</strong> Less fertile time
                      (after ovulation and before menstruation)
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>High, soft, open:</strong> Fertile time (around
                      ovulation)
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    To check cervical position, wash hands thoroughly, then
                    insert one or two fingers into the vagina to feel for the
                    cervix. Consistency in checking at the same time each day is
                    important.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-warning">
                    <em
                      >Note: This method requires practice and may not be
                      suitable for everyone.</em
                    >
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingSecondaryFertilitySigns">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseSecondaryFertilitySigns"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseSecondaryFertilitySigns"
                >
                  Secondary Fertility Signs
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseSecondaryFertilitySigns"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingSecondaryFertilitySigns"
                data-bs-parent="#fertilityAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    Some women notice other bodily changes around ovulation that
                    can serve as secondary fertility indicators:
                  </p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Mittelschmerz:</strong> One-sided lower abdominal
                      pain/cramping when an egg is released
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Increased libido:</strong> Many women experience
                      heightened sex drive around ovulation
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Breast tenderness:</strong> Sensitivity or
                      tenderness in breasts
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Heightened senses:</strong> Increased sense of
                      smell, taste, or vision
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Spotting:</strong> Light spotting can occur when
                      the egg bursts from the follicle
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Bloating:</strong> Some women experience water
                      retention
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    These signs alone aren't reliable for fertility tracking but
                    can provide additional confirmation when used alongside
                    primary fertility signs.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-4 mt-4 mt-lg-0">
      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Your Fertility Stats</h5>
          <div class="cycle-stats">
            <div class="row mb-3">
              <div class="col-12 mb-3">
                <small class="text-muted">Next Predicted Ovulation</small>
                <h4>July 19, 2023</h4>
              </div>
              <div class="col-12">
                <small class="text-muted">Fertile Window</small>
                <h4>July 16-22, 2023</h4>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="progress mb-2" style="height: 25px">
              <div
                class="progress-bar bg-secondary"
                role="progressbar"
                style="width: 25%"
                aria-valuenow="25"
                aria-valuemin="0"
                aria-valuemax="100"
              >
                Menstruation
              </div>
              <div
                class="progress-bar bg-info"
                role="progressbar"
                style="width: 35%"
                aria-valuenow="35"
                aria-valuemin="0"
                aria-valuemax="100"
              >
                Follicular
              </div>
              <div
                class="progress-bar bg-warning"
                role="progressbar"
                style="width: 5%"
                aria-valuenow="5"
                aria-valuemin="0"
                aria-valuemax="100"
              >
                Ovulation
              </div>
              <div
                class="progress-bar bg-success"
                role="progressbar"
                style="width: 35%"
                aria-valuenow="35"
                aria-valuemin="0"
                aria-valuemax="100"
              >
                Luteal
              </div>
            </div>
            <small class="text-muted"
              >Current phase: Follicular (Pre-Ovulation)</small
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Fertility Reminder</h5>
          <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
            <h6 class="alert-heading">Your Fertility Window Is Coming!</h6>
            <p>
              Your predicted fertile window starts in 3 days. This is the
              optimal time for conception if you're trying to get pregnant.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-0">
              Remember to track your BBT and cervical mucus daily for most
              accurate predictions.
            </p>
          </div>
          <button class="btn btn-outline-primary w-100">
            Set Fertility Reminders
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Fertility Tips</h5>

          <div class="cycle-tip mb-3">
            <h6>Optimizing Conception Chances</h6>
            <p>
              Have intercourse every 1-2 days during your fertile window,
              especially the 2-3 days before ovulation, for the highest chances
              of conception.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="cycle-tip mb-3">
            <h6>Understanding Sperm Viability</h6>
            <p>
              Sperm can survive up to 5 days in fertile cervical fluid, which is
              why the days before ovulation are optimal for conception.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="cycle-tip">
            <h6>Balancing Timing & Enjoyment</h6>
            <p>
              While timing is important, excessive stress about perfect timing
              can negatively impact fertility. Try to maintain a balance between
              tracking and spontaneity.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Related Resources</h5>
          <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
            <li class="list-group-item">
              <a href="/menstrual_cycle">Menstrual Cycle Tracking</a>
